              <button
                type="button"
                class="toggle-btn"
                data-target="design-v2"
                style="padding:0.35rem 0.5rem; border-radius:6px;"
              >
                View HTML
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div id="design-v2" style="margin-top:0.5rem; display:none;">
            <iframe
              src={`${base}/documents/ADEN_docs/html/Elevator Simulation Updog Design Document, v2/ElevatorSimulationUpdogDesignDocumentv2.html`}
              style="width:100%; height:520px; border:1px solid #ddd; border-radius:6px;"
              loading="lazy"
              title="Design Document v2"
            ></iframe>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ANALYSIS -->
    <section id="analysis" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
      <h2>Summary of Analysis</h2>

      <p>During analysis, three elevator configurations were compared:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Capacity = 15, floorTicks = 5, doorTicks = 2, passPerTick = 3</li>
        <li>Capacity = 20, floorTicks = 7, doorTicks = 3, passPerTick = 4</li>
        <li>Capacity = 10, floorTicks = 3, doorTicks = 2, passPerTick = 3</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We evaluated completion rate, average wait time, average total time,
        weighted passenger travel time, ride time per floor, and standard deviation metrics.
      </p>

      <p>
        All three elevators achieved excellent completion rates, but
        Configuration 3 consistently provided the fastest service and most reliable passenger experience.
      </p>

      <p>
        Although Configuration 3 had the smallest capacity, its faster movement
        and higher throughput outweighed the larger designs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- LEARNINGS -->
    <section id="learnings" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
      <h2>Key Learnings</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Finite state machines provide a structured framework for embedded control systems.</li>
        <li>Data-driven analysis is essential when comparing competing designs.</li>
        <li>Smaller-capacity systems can outperform larger systems when optimized for throughput.</li>
        <li>User-facing metrics such as wait time and consistency are critical indicators of quality.</li>
        <li>Simulation is a valuable engineering tool for evaluating designs before deployment.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- REFLECTIONS -->
    <section id="reflections" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <h2>Reflections</h2>

    <!-- Reflection 1 -->
    <div style="border:1px solid #eee; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; margin-top:0.75rem;">
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
        <strong>Elevator Reflection 1</strong>

        <div style="display:flex; gap:0.5rem; align-items:center;">
          <a
            href={`${base}/documents/reflections/pdf/${encodeURIComponent('Elevator Reflection 1.pdf')}`}
            download
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            style="font-size:0.9rem; color:#0b66c3;"
          >
            Download PDF
          </a>

          <button
            type="button"
            class="toggle-btn"
            data-target="ref-1"
            style="padding:0.35rem 0.5rem; border-radius:6px;"
          >
            View HTML
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="ref-1" style="margin-top:0.5rem; display:none;">
        <iframe
          src={`${base}/documents/reflections/html/${encodeURIComponent('Elevator Reflection 1.html')}`}
          style="width:100%; height:520px; border:1px solid #ddd; border-radius:6px;"
          loading="lazy"
          title="Elevator Reflection 1"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Reflection 2 -->
    <div style="border:1px solid #eee; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; margin-top:0.75rem;">
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
        <strong>Elevator Weekly Reflection 2</strong>

        <div style="display:flex; gap:0.5rem; align-items:center;">
          <a
